From 80fc4c57fbf8333d9af86af687a10158dd23dc11 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: apannerselva <apannerselva@marvell.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 11:21:43 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] EVPN MH FRR patch

Why I did it
=============
HLD: EVPN VXLAN Multihoming HLD

This PR integrates the EVPN VXLAN Multihoming (EVPN-MH) feature into
the SONiC build system by:

- Updating submodule pointers to EVPN-MH enabled versions
- Adding FRR 10.5.1 with EVPN-MH patches
- Building custom iproute2 package with protocol field support
- Adding YANG models for EVPN-MH configuration
- Configuring FRR/zebra for external MAC learning mode

This is the master integration PR that pulls together all EVPN-MH
component PRs into a buildable SONiC image.

How I did it
=============

1. Submodule Updates - Point to EVPN-MH enabled versions:
   - sonic-swss-common: L2 nexthop group table and raw netlink handling
   - sonic-swss: EVPN-MH orchestration agents (EvpnMhOrch, ShlOrch,
     FdbOrch enhancements)
   - sonic-utilities: EVPN-MH CLI commands
   - sonic-linux-kernel: Kernel patches for extended flags and protocol
   - frr: FRR 10.5.1 with EVPN-MH support

2. FRR 10.5.1 Integration with EVPN-MH Patches:
   Rebased to FRR 10.5.1 and added EVPN-MH specific patches:

   0025-zebra-EVPN-VXLAN-Multihome-extern-mode-Enable-kernel.patch
     Enable kernel MAC external learn mode for EVPN-MH, support for
     --kernel-mac-ext-learn zebra option, handles externally learned
     MACs from kernel with proper aging (217 lines)

   0026-zebra-Use-protocol-RTPROT_HW-for-hardware-learnt-MAC.patch
     Use RTPROT_HW protocol for hardware-learned MACs, distinguishes
     data plane vs control plane MAC learning (42 lines)

   0027-zebra-doc-update-for-zebra-option-kernel-mac-ext.patch
     Documentation for --kernel-mac-ext-learn option (39 lines)

   0028-zebra-EVPN-VXLAN-MH-extern-mode-Update-debug-print-f.patch
     Enhanced debug logging for EVPN-MH operations (52 lines)

   0029-zebra-ARP-ND-Suppression-disabled-for-kernel-mac-ext.patch
     Disable ARP/ND suppression in external learn mode (53 lines)

   0030-fdbsyncd-netlink-message-handling-for-mac_extern_learn.patch
     Netlink message handling for external MAC learning, protocol
     field propagation (224 lines)

   0031-fdbsync-update-del-expiry-in-extern_learn-mod.patch
     MAC expiry handling in external learn mode (232 lines)

   0032-tests-topotests-EVPN-VXLAN-MH-extern-learn-mode-test.patch
     Comprehensive topotests for EVPN-MH external learn mode (1850 lines)

   0033-bgpd-install-evpn-failure-logging.patch
     Enhanced logging for EVPN route installation failures (47 lines)

   Modified frr.mk and Makefile for FRR 10.5.1 build configuration.
   Removed obsolete patches: Cleaned up 40+ patches that were upstreamed
   or no longer needed in FRR 10.5.1.

3. iproute2 Package Build with Protocol Field Support:
   Built custom iproute2 6.1.0-3 package for EVPN-MH:

   New build infrastructure: iproute2.mk, Makefile, patch directory

   Patches applied:
   - 0001-ext-nda-flags-mh-peer.patch (56 lines)
     NDA_FLAGS_EXT support for MH peer sync
   - 0002-bridge-fdb-Protocol-field-in-bridge-fdb.patch (82 lines)
     Protocol field in bridge FDB commands
   - cross-compile-changes.patch (13 lines)
     Cross-compilation fixes

   Docker integration: Modified all bookworm-based Docker images to use
   locally built iproute2. Removed apt-get install iproute2 from:
   docker-base-bookworm, docker-orchagent, docker-fpm-frr, docker-sonic-vs,
   docker-syncd-vs, docker-gbsyncd-vs.
   Added IPROUTE2 dependency to docker-base-bookworm.mk.

4. YANG Models for EVPN-MH Configuration (sonic-yang-models):
   Added comprehensive YANG schemas for EVPN-MH configuration:

   New file: sonic-evpn.yang (151 lines):
   - EVPN_ETHERNET_SEGMENT table:
     ifname (PORT/PORTCHANNEL ref), esi (AUTO or manual),
     type (TYPE_0_OPERATOR_CONFIGURED, TYPE_3_MAC_BASED),
     df_pref (1-65535, default 32767)
   - EVPN_MH_GLOBAL table:
     startup_delay (0-3600s, default 300),
     mac_holdtime (0-86400s, default 1080),
     neigh_holdtime (0-86400s, default 1080)

   Modified: sonic-portchannel.yang (+9 lines):
   - Added es_id field for Ethernet Segment ID on PortChannels
   - Added system_mac field for Type 3 ESI generation

   Testing: Comprehensive YANG model tests added.

5. FRR Configuration Changes:
   Modified zebra startup to enable external MAC learning:
   Added --kernel-mac-ext-learn flag to zebra command line.
   This enables zebra to accept externally learned MAC addresses,
   properly handle MAC aging/expiry, and synchronize MAC state
   between kernel and FRR.

6. Build System Updates:
   - .gitmodules: Updated submodule URLs and branches for evpn_mh
   - slave.mk: Added iproute2 to build dependencies
   - sonic-utilities-data.mk: Fixed build dependency on sonic_utilities
   - Dockerfile.j2: Updated for iproute2 dependency

7. Sample Configuration:
   Updated sample_config_db.json with EVPN-MH examples including
   EVPN_MH_GLOBAL and EVPN_ETHERNET_SEGMENT table entries.

How to verify it
=================

1. Build SONiC image with EVPN-MH:
   make init
   make configure PLATFORM=vs
   make SONIC_BUILD_JOBS=8 target/sonic-vs.img.gz

2. Verify submodule versions:
   git submodule status | grep -E "sonic-swss|sonic-utilities|sonic-frr"

3. Verify iproute2 package:
   ls target/debs/bookworm/iproute2_*.deb
   dpkg -l | grep iproute2  # Should show locally built version
   bridge fdb add 00:00:00:00:00:88 dev <intf> vlan 1000 master \
     dynamic extern_learn proto hw
   bridge -d fdb show | grep 00:00:00:00:00:88

4. Verify FRR 10.5.1 with EVPN-MH:
   show version  # Should show FRR 10.5.1
   ps aux | grep zebra  # Should include --kernel-mac-ext-learn
   vtysh -c "show evpn es"
   vtysh -c "show evpn es-evi"

5. Verify YANG models:
   cd src/sonic-yang-models
   python3 -m pytest tests/yang_model_tests/tests/evpn.json -v
   python3 -m pytest tests/yang_model_tests/tests_config/evpn.json -v

6. End-to-end EVPN-MH testing:
   config evpn-mh startup-delay 300
   config evpn-mh mac-holdtime 1080
   config evpn-mh neigh-holdtime 1080
   config interface evpn-esi add PortChannel1 \
     00:01:02:03:04:05:06:07:08:09
   config interface evpn-df-pref PortChannel1 50000
   show evpn es
   show evpn es-evi
   redis-cli -n 4 HGETALL "EVPN_ETHERNET_SEGMENT|PortChannel1"

7. Integration testing:
   - Multi-homing topology with ES peers
   - MAC learning and synchronization
   - DF election verification
   - Split-horizon functionality
   - Failover scenarios

Description for the changelog
==============================
Add EVPN VXLAN Multihoming build integration: FRR 10.5.1 with
EVPN-MH patches, custom iproute2 with protocol field support,
YANG models for EVPN-MH configuration, submodule updates, and
zebra external MAC learning mode.

Depends on
===========
- sonic-linux-kernel PR #540: Kernel patches for EVPN-MH
- sonic-swss-common PR: L2 nexthop group table and raw netlink
- sonic-swss PR: EVPN-MH orchestration agents
- sonic-utilities PR: EVPN-MH CLI commands
- iproute2 patches for protocol field support

